result.name: Hot in A Pot

reviews.text: A small hotpot shop in Tin Hau area serving very good seafood as well as beef shabu shabu. Foods are fresh and delicious and the shop is always crowded in the evening. You need to finish your round in 2 hours. The drawback is the rather compacted seating environment. Price is moderately expensive.
Nice dimsum! Can't find anywhere else
Always like this place in tin hau, good quality food and especially in small group, you can order half portion. There dim sum is good and reasonable price too.
Seating is quite cramped but the food is quite good
good price and delicious dish

result.name: 滾得棧

reviews.text: 午巿點心幾好味😋
一定要試花膠雞湯底哦，d花膠有手指咁長又厚身……超正👍，飲埋d湯非常滋潤。牛肉都非常正，海鮮、丸類、餃子都好味，連庶汁都好飲，因為係自家制做。有水準值得再試。
🧑🏻美食很精緻，味道滿意，但環境整潔度及布局尚有改善空間❣️
點心不錯，坐位太迫。
肉鮮，湯底也很讚
